<div class="why-page faq-page">

  <p class="why-eyebrow">SINISTER STASH</p>

  <h1 class="why-title">FAQ</h1>

  <div class="why-divider"></div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">Do you sell firearms?</h2>
    <p>No. We sell stickers, patches, apparel, and range gear. We do not sell firearms, registered lowers, ammunition, or anything that requires an FFL. We make the culture stuff. The things you put on your range bag, your kit, your jacket, your laptop. The things that say <em>I'm here and I'm not hiding.</em></p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">Do you ship internationally?</h2>
    <p>Yes, we ship internationally for most products. That includes apparel, stickers, and patches. For items classified as firearm accessories, we're limited to the United States only due to export regulations. Each product page will note if an item is US-only.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">Are your stickers weatherproof?</h2>
    <p>Yes. All of our stickers are die-cut vinyl. They're weatherproof, UV resistant, and dishwasher safe. Slap them on your range bag, water bottle, car, pelican case, whatever. They hold up.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">What sizes do your tees come in?</h2>
    <p>XS through 3XL. We're not interested in a brand that only fits some of us. Sizing details are listed on each product page. If something runs small or large, we'll note it there.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">What's your return policy?</h2>
    <p>Standard returns on non-customized items. If it's unworn, unwashed, and in original condition, you can return it within 30 days for a refund. Custom or personalized items are final sale. Full details on our <a href="/policies/refund-policy">Shipping & Returns</a> page.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">Is this brand really queer-owned?</h2>
    <p>Yes. Queer, disabled, and leftist. This isn't a corporate pride campaign or a marketing angle. This is our actual life. We built Sinister Stash because we walked into gun culture and found nothing that reflected who we are. So we made it ourselves.</p>
    <p>You can read the full story on our <a href="/pages/why">Why</a> page.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">What's Sacred Iron Co.?</h2>
    <p>Our sibling brand. Sinister Stash does stickers, patches, and apparel. Sacred Iron Co. does engraved goods and range gear. That's the heavier, more personalized stuff. Same people, same values, different product lines. Both are launching soon.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">How do I use my discount code?</h2>
    <p>Enter it at checkout in the discount code field. If you signed up for our email list, your code is <strong>LOADUP10</strong> for 10% off your first order. Codes can't be combined with other offers.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="why-section">
    <h2 class="why-heading">I have a question that's not here.</h2>
    <p>Hit us up on our <a href="/pages/contact">Contact</a> page. We're real people and we actually respond.</p>
  </div>

</div>

